(569,'RIG-IMP-0569',742,'Unknown','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Concord, NC • Pensacola, FL • Appleton, WI • Dayton, OH • Lake Elsinore, CA • Vancouver, WA • Montréal, QC\nSoutheast Service Center\n704.509.9393\nwww.oasisalignment.com\nOASIS Proposal\nCustomer: Tekni-Plex, Inc\nPrepared For: Mr. Dan Marr Prepared By: Derry Steedley\nProposal No.: 35434-56791 Proposal Type: Time & Materials\nProposal Date: August 21, 2018 Proposal Valid Until: November 19, 2018\nProject Scope\nDates of Service: August 21, 2018 Date is for proposal purpose only.\nEquipment to be Serviced: New Laminator & Two Slitters Alignment Support\nLaminator and Slitters Alignment\n OASIS will provide One Metrology Engineer to support the Alignment of the Laminator and the Two\nSlitters working Twelve hour shifts on Two Weekdays.\n OASIS will supply a technical report (with drawings) documenting the services performed and providing\nrecommendations for corrective action where required.\nProject Resources\nStaffing\n Team A: One-Metrology Engineer\nShift Schedule\n Team A: Working 2 weekdays at 12 hours per shift\nEquipment\n 1 Van\n 1 Laser Tracker\nProject Costs\nLabor: $7,322\nEquipment: $4,906\nExpenses: $665\nTotal Cost: $12,893 (Time & Materials; Net 45 Days)\nPlus state and local taxes where applicable\nThis Proposal contains CONFIDENTIAL and proprietary information of OASIS (including without limitation, pricing, scheduling, and staffing information)\nand you hereby agree not to disclose it without the prior written consent of OASIS except internally in connection with services rendered by OASIS.\n1 of 3\nSoutheast Service Center\n704.509.9393\nwww.oasisalignment.com\nConditions Required to Perform Service\n OASIS will be provided with reasonably free and unobstructed access to the components of the machine\nas required.\n The customer will provide all lockout and tag-out procedures to ensure the safety of OASIS personnel.\n Customer must supply electrical power outlet (110V, 15A) in the immediate vicinity of the work site.\nAdditional Notes\n Unless otherwise specified, this proposal assumes resources will come from our nearest Regional Service\nCenter. Prompt confirmation is required in order to allocate these resources. Otherwise, the necessary\nresources and tooling may need to come from another Regional Service Center, which could result in\nadditional costs related to travel and expenses.\n This proposal DOES NOT include work on weekend days or holidays.\nTerms and Conditions\n Projects exceeding a month in duration as well as projects having more than seven days between service\nvisits and which span calendar months will be invoiced on a monthly basis.\n The terms of payment are Net 45 Days.\n Our performance of these services is conditional upon the “OASIS Alignment Services, LLC Terms and\nConditions” which can be found on the following page.\nRochester, NH • Concord, NC • Pensacola, FL • Appleton, WI • Dayton, OH • Lake Elsinore, CA • Vancouver, WA • Montréal, QC\n2 of 3\nOASIS Alignment Services, LLC\nTerms and Conditions\nThese Terms and Conditions constitute the complete understanding of the Parties with respect to the matters addressed herein (the \"Terms\") and together with the proposal\nattached hereto (the \"Proposal\") constitute the entire agreement of the Parties with respect to the Services (the \"Agreement\"). The Parties as referred to herein are the\nCustomer as identified on the Proposal (the “Customer”) and OASIS Alignment Services, LLC (\"OASIS\"). The Parties hereby agree that:\n1. SCOPE OF SERVICES. The services to be provided by OASIS shall be limited to the services described in the Proposal (the \"Services\").\n2. FORCE MAJEURE/ DELAY. Schedule dates are approximate and neither party hereto shall be liable for any losses or damages of any nature whatsoever incurred\nor suffered as a result of any failure or delay in performance due to any cause or circumstance beyond its reasonable control, including, without limitation, Acts of God,\nfire, war, terrorism, riot, explosion, accident, casualty, flood, inability to obtain fuel, power, labor or transportation facilities, governmental laws, regulations or orders,\nbreakage or failure of machinery or apparatus, or labor trouble, strike, lockout or injunction. Should OASIS be delayed due to the negligent acts or omissions of the\nCustomer, its officers, employees or agents, interference by other parties or inaccessibility of plant, property or equipment, in addition to the schedule being modified, a\nchange order shall be issued to reimburse OASIS for costs incurred to re-establish the schedule. OASIS will make all reasonable efforts to ensure that the timeliness of our\nwork is consistent with our commitment, the term “time is of the essence” does not apply.\n3. LICENSES AND PERMITS. Customer shall bear the cost of all local licenses and permits necessary to the performance of the Services and shall procure, with the\nassistance of OASIS, such licenses and permits.\n4. LIABILITY. (a) OASIS shall indemnify and save Customer harmless from and against liability imposed by law upon Customer arising out of claims from third\nparties for damages as a result of accidental bodily injury (including death) or damage to tangible property to the extent caused by the negligence or willful misconduct of\nOASIS or its employees in performance of the Services. (b) Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, OASIS shall not be liable to Customer under the Agreement\nor otherwise, and Customer shall indemnify and save OASIS harmless from and against any and all such liability, whether the claim be in contract, negligence, strict\nliability, other tort or any other theory or cause of action: (1) for losses, liabilities, damages, costs or expenses (i) arising out of bodily injury (including death) to any\nperson or damage (including loss of use) to any property to the extent caused by or resulting from the negligence or willful misconduct of Customer, its officers,\nemployees or agents, or (ii) which exceed the dollar limits or coverage of insurance specified in Paragraph 5 below, or (2) for loss of use, loss of profits, business\ninterruption or consequential, indirect or incidental damages and regardless of whether any such loss or claim arises out of breach of contract or warranty, tort, product\nliability, indemnity, contribution, strict liability or any other legal theory.\n5. INSURANCE. Throughout the term of this Agreement, OASIS shall procure and maintain the following minimum insurance coverage: (1) Commercial General\nLiability Policy, including Contractual Liability ($1,000,000 per occurrence, and $2,000,000 in the aggregate); (2) Comprehensive Automobile Liability Policy\n($1,000,000 per accident, combined single limit); and (3) Worker’s Compensation Policy (statutory requirement).\n6. WARRANTY. All work furnished by OASIS in accordance with the Proposal shall be free of material defects for a period of ninety (90) days from completion of the\nwork. In the event of any failure to conform to this Warranty, OASIS shall at its option and expense either repair the defect, correct the service or provide a replacement\npart (only if such part was provided by OASIS). OASIS shall not be responsible for costs of dismantling or reassembling the product. THE WARRANTIES SET FORTH\nIN THIS PARAGRAPH 6 ARE OASIS’ SOLE AND EXCLUSIVE WARRANTIES. OASIS MAKES NO OTHER WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND\nWHATSOEVER, EXPRESS, IMPLIED, ORAL, WRITTEN OR OTHERWISE INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION, WARRANTIES OF\nMERCHANTABILITY OR FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. IN NO EVENT SHALL OASIS OR ANY OF ITS DIRECTORS, OFFICERS,\nEMPLOYEES, AGENTS OR AFFILIATES BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, RELIANCE OR CONSEQUENTIAL DAMAGES INCLUDING,\nWITHOUT LIMITATION, DAMAGES ARISING FROM CLAIMS RELATED TO LOSS OF PROFITS OR REVENUE, LOSS OF USE OF EQUIPMENT OR\nOTHER DOWN TIME COSTS, WHETHER CLAIMED BY REASON OF BREACH OF WARRANTY, BREACH OF CONTRACT, INDEMINITY,\nCONTRIBUTION OR OTHERWISE.\n7. EXCLUSIVITY. Notwithstanding anything herein to the contrary, the rights and remedies specifically set forth in this Agreement are the sole and exclusive rights\nand remedies available to the Customer.\n8. GOVERNING LAW. The Agreement shall be governed and construed in accordance with the internal laws of the State of New Hampshire, without regard to\nconflict of laws principles.\n9. GENERAL PROVISIONS. (a) Property. All data, calculations, reports, manuals and drawings will remain the property of OASIS and may not be reproduced,\nexcept for the Customer\'s use, or transmitted or disclosed to any party other than employees of the Customer without the prior written consent of OASIS. (b) Notice. All\nnotices to OASIS shall be directed to OASIS Alignment Services, LLC, Attn: President, 255 Pickering Road, Rochester, NH 03867. All notices to Customer will be\ndirected to the Customer address stated on the Proposal. (c) Entire Agreement. This Agreement supersedes all previous agreements and understandings between the\nParties of any nature whatsoever, verbal or written, and constitutes the entire understanding between the Parties. The scheduling of OASIS services by the Customer shall\nbe deemed acceptance of the Proposal and these Terms notwithstanding any conflicting terms and conditions provided with any purchase order or otherwise. (d)\nSeverability. Each paragraph of the Agreement is severable from the entire Agreement and if one provision hereof is declared invalid, the remaining provisions shall\nnevertheless remain in effect.\nRevision of May 2006\n3 of 3',NULL,10,'Contract',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,0.00,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL,0,'{\"source_file\":\"sales_quote-75340.pdf\",\"quote_date_raw\":\"Southeast Service Center\",\"quote_date_iso\":null,\"recipient\":{\"name\":null,\"company\":null,\"address\":null,\"email\":null,\"phone\":null},\"work_scope\":null,\"scope_items\":[\"Concord, NC • Pensacola, FL • App